The paper discusses the optimization properties of neural networks, specifically one-hidden-layer neural networks with ReLU activation. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the theoretical guarantees of neural networks, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the potential applications of neural networks in computer vision (cs.CV) and regularization techniques (cs.SI).
